description.narrative: To establish the basis for viable irrigated agriculture and natural resources management in four main irrigation sites and their surrounding watersheds: (i) Andapa (Sava Region), (ii) Marovoay (Boeny Region), (iii) Itasy Region, and (iv) Lac Alaotra (Alaotra Mangoro Region).

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2,10(b) | Description :ensure that DGDR recruits international technical assistance specialists for thepreparation of the Watershed Master Plans in each of the Project Areas | Due Date :22-Feb-2007

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2,10(c) | Description :ensure that within 90 days after effective date, a MOU, 1 per project area, beentered into by MAEP through NIWMP and MINENVEF through the 3rd Env. Support Program | Due Date :31-Jul-2007
Finance Agreement :Schedule 2,10(e) | Description :issue, by December 31, 2007, and thereafter implement legislative guidelines forthe application of the new seeds legislation | Due Date :30-Jun-2013
Finance Agreement :Schedule 2,10(f) | Description :a baseline survey for the Project be completed by December 31, 2006 | Due Date:31-Dec-2006
Finance Agreement :Schedule 2,10(g) | Description :the watershed Master Plans, one per Project Area, be completed by September 30,2007 | Due Date :31-Jul-2008
Finance Agreement :Schedule 2,10(h) | Description :operational modalities of management and replenishment of FERHA be defined bySeptember 30, 2007 | Due Date :16-Jun-2014
Finance Agreement :Shedule 2,10(d) | Description :adopt, by December 31, 2006, and thereafter implement a national strategy onfertilizers | Due Date :31-Dec-2006

Finance Agreement :Shedule 2,10(i) | Description :the irrigation related legal framework, including but not limited to Law 90-016and subsequent implementation texts be harmonized with the provisions of the Program | Due Date :13-Jun-2014
